{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17620002","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17620002"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T15:39:41+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T15:39:41+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16603"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"16603","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/16603"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.06,0.32,0,0.26,0.35]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9294"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"76347"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"9294","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/9294"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16603"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61856"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"22"},{"type":"tags","id":"23"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4155"},{"type":"tags","id":"4166"},{"type":"tags","id":"4929"},{"type":"tags","id":"4935"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"4943"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"5251"},{"type":"tags","id":"5315"},{"type":"tags","id":"10106"},{"type":"tags","id":"10145"},{"type":"tags","id":"10604"},{"type":"tags","id":"10631"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"22009"},{"type":"contributions","id":"22459"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"76347","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/76347"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 28-year-old woman presents with a two-year history of infertility. She has irregular menstrual cycles and is not ovulating regularly. Her doctor prescribes clomiphene to induce ovulation.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the mechanism of action of clomiphene?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Blocks progesterone receptors in the endometrium","Blocks oestrogen receptors in the hypothalamus","Inhibits follicle-stimulating hormone release","Increases oestrogen production from the ovaries","Directly stimulates ovarian follicle development"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBlocking oestrogen receptors in the hypothalamus\u003C/strong\u003E is the primary mechanism of action of clomiphene to stimulate ovulation. It is a selective oestrogen receptor modulator (SERM). By preventing oestrogen from binding to hypothalamic receptors, clomiphene interrupts the negative feedback loop that normally suppresses gonadotropin-releasing hormone (GnRH). This leads to increased secretion of follicle-stimulating hormone (FSH) and luteinizing hormone (LH) from the anterior pituitary. The increased gonadotropin levels stimulate ovarian follicle development and ovulation, making clomiphene useful for treating anovulatory infertility.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EClomiphene works indirectly through increasing gonadotropins; it does not \u003Cstrong\u003Edirectly stimulate ovarian follicle development.\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EI\u003Cstrong\u003Encreased oestrogen production from the ovaries\u003C/strong\u003E is not how clomiphene works.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EClomiphene actually increases rather than \u003Cstrong\u003Einhibits\u003C/strong\u003E \u003Cstrong\u003Efollicle-stimulating hormone release.\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EClomiphene is a SERM, and therefore dose not \u003Cstrong\u003Eblock progesterone receptors in the endometrium. \u003C/strong\u003EIt does have actions at oestrogen receptors in the vagina, cervix and uterus.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Clomiphene acts as a selective oestrogen receptor modulator that blocks oestrogen receptors in the hypothalamus.","Clomiphene blocks hypothalamic oestrogen receptors to prevent negative feedback, leading to increased gonadotropin-releasing hormone secretion.","Increased gonadotropin release stimulates ovarian follicle development and ovulation."],"references":["Therapeutic Guidelines. Melbourne: Therapeutic Guidelines Limited. Available from: https://www.tg.org.au","Ritter J, Flower RJ (Rod J), Henderson G (Graeme), et al.\u00a0Rang and Dale\u2019s Pharmacology. Tenth edition. Elsevier; 2024.","Australian Medicines Handbook\u00a0(online). Adelaide: Australian Medicines Handbook Pty Ltd. Available from:\u00a0https://amhonline.amh.net.au/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61856"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16603"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61856","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/61856"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-03T08:53:57+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-03T08:54:20+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9294"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"76347"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"22","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/22"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udf53","name":"Gynaecology","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"3"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"23","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/23"},"attributes":{"